                            <comment id="14459576" author="spullara" created="Sun, 23 Nov 2003 17:22:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Heredocs/verbatim/reports whatever you want to call them are implemented.  The syntax is &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;TOKEN\n....text....\nTOKEN  They act just like double quoted GStrings so you can use them for large template text quite easily:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;println(&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;EOS&lt;br/&gt;
Hello there!&lt;br/&gt;
EOS)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is exactly the same as&lt;br/&gt;
println(&quot;Hello there!&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Notice there are no trailing or prefixed new lines.  You can see other examples in VerbatimGStringTest.groovy.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
